Jane Grey (actress) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jane_Grey_(actress) 0 Jane Grey (May 22, 1883 or 1888 – November 9, 1944) was an American stage and screen actress. She was the original female lead in the popular 1914 stage play Kick In with Forest Winant and John Barrymore, and also acted in a variety of other Broadway work. She appeared in Hassard Short's All-Star Shakespearean pageant for Actor's Equity in 1921. Her film career pertains to the silent film era in which she appeared in a few French made films for Louis Feuillade in the early 20s. She was married twice, to Ricardo Martin and to William E.
